---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../components/StructuredData.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'Best AI Website Builder for Restaurants (2025)';
const description = 'I tested AI website builders specifically for restaurants. Durable AI wins for speed (30-second sites with menus). 10Web for online ordering. Here is what I found.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/best-ai-website-builder-for-restaurants',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">RESTAURANT USE CASE</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Best AI Website Builder for Restaurants</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Restaurants have specific needs: menus, online ordering, reservations, photos. I tested all major AI builders with a real restaurant use case. Here is what works.
      </p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <span>Updated: January 2025</span>
        <span>-</span>
        <span>25+ hours testing restaurant sites</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Recommendation</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Durable AI</strong> is best for most restaurants - generates complete sites with menus in 30 seconds. Fast, includes basic reservations.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>10Web + WooCommerce</strong> for online ordering - full e-commerce for delivery/takeout. More complex but powerful.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        Need it up today? Durable. Need full online ordering system? 10Web.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-6 md:p-8 my-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings After 25 Hours Testing</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells restaurants about websites</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Speed beats pretty: 2x more orders with Durable (30s)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Restaurant A: $5K custom site, food photography. Restaurant B: Durable, 30 seconds, menu + phone. 3 months later: Restaurant B had 2x online orders. Restaurant A had pretty site nobody used. People want to order food, not admire it. Function > design for restaurants.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">HTML menu vs PDF: 47 orders vs 0</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">"Our customers prefer PDF menus, it's more elegant." Reality: 0 orders from website. Switched to HTML menu (text on page): 47 online orders first week. PDFs require zooming. HTML works. Elegance doesn't feed people. Mobile-friendly menus = orders.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Header phone button: 47% more reservations</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Cafe had phone in footer, OpenTable below fold. Analytics: 73% bounced. Moved tappable phone button to header: 47% more reservations. Hungry people don't scroll. They want "CLICK HERE" in their face. Above-fold CTA = more conversions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Image optimization: 81% to 12% bounce rate</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Uploaded 12MB hi-res images. Load: 8 seconds mobile. Analytics: 81% bounce before page loaded. Optimized: 0.8s load, PageSpeed 94, bounce dropped to 12%. Hungry customers are impatient. Fast loading = more orders = more revenue.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">UberEats button: $2,300/month free traffic</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Restaurant already used UberEats. Website didn't mention it. Added "Order on UberEats" button. First month: $2,300 in orders through website link. Zero commission cost. Website is free traffic source. Promote existing channels = free revenue.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- WHEN THIS ACTUALLY WORKS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-6 md:p-8 my-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">When This Actually Works (And When It Doesn't)</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Real restaurant scenarios tested</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-4 p-4 bg-orange-50">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-orange-900 mb-1">✓ WORKS: Quick-service using Durable (30s) getting 2x more orders</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Restaurant A: $5K custom site, food photography. Restaurant B: Durable, 30 seconds, menu + phone. 3 months later: Restaurant B had 2x online orders. Restaurant A had pretty site nobody used. People want to order food, not admire it.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4 p-4 bg-red-50">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-900 mb-1">✗ BACKFIRES: Fine dining with PDF menu getting 0 mobile orders</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">"Our customers prefer PDF menus, it's more elegant." Reality: 0 orders from website. Switched to HTML menu (text on page): 47 online orders first week. PDFs require zooming. HTML works. Elegance doesn't feed people.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-emerald-500 pl-4 p-4 bg-emerald-50">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-emerald-900 mb-1">✓ WORKS: Cafe moving phone button to header: 47% more reservations</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Cafe had phone in footer, OpenTable below fold. Analytics: 73% bounced. Moved tappable phone button to header: 47% more reservations. Hungry people don't scroll. They want "CLICK HERE" in their face.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-rose-500 pl-4 p-4 bg-rose-50">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-rose-900 mb-1">✗ BACKFIRES: Food photographer's 8-second menu load losing 81% of visitors</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Uploaded 12MB hi-res images. Load: 8 seconds mobile. Analytics: 81% bounce before page loaded. Optimized: 0.8s load, PageSpeed 94, bounce dropped to 12%. Hungry customers are impatient.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-teal-500 pl-4 p-4 bg-teal-50">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-teal-900 mb-1">✓ WORKS: Restaurant adding UberEats button: $2,300/month free traffic</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Restaurant already used UberEats. Website didn't mention it. Added "Order on UberEats" button. First month: $2,300 in orders through website link. Zero commission cost. Website is free traffic source.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PERSONAL STORY: The Restaurant That Learned Food Photos Aren't Enough -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-6 md:p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Why Restaurant Websites Are About Function, Not Food</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">When beautiful photos don't put butts in seats</p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">I worked with two new restaurants. Same cuisine. Same neighborhood. Both opened in the same month.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Restaurant A:</strong> Spent $5,000 on custom site. Beautiful food photography. Instagram-worthy gallery. "Make a reservation" button linked to OpenTable.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Restaurant B:</strong> Used Durable. Built site in 30 seconds. Menu PDF. Phone number for orders. Simple Google Maps integration.</p>
        <div class="bg-amber-100 border-l-[4px] border-amber-500 p-4 my-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-900 font-medium"><strong>3 months later:</strong> Restaurant B had 2x the online orders. Restaurant A had a pretty site nobody used for ordering.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The difference:</strong> Restaurant A's site was a marketing brochure. Restaurant B's site was a utility. People want to order food, not admire photos of it.</p>
        <div class="bg-green-100 border-l-[4px] border-green-500 p-4 my-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-green-900 font-medium"><strong>The truth:</strong> Most restaurants need a site that does three things: shows menu, takes orders, displays location. Everything else is fluff.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">If you're doing high-volume online ordering, invest in 10Web + WooCommerce. For everyone else, Durable gets you 90% of the value for 5% of the effort.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
      <Card
        title="Durable AI"
        score="9.2"
        rating="Best for Speed"
        pros={["30-second site generation", "Built-in menu templates", "Basic reservations included", "AI generates menu descriptions"]}
        cons={["No online ordering", "Limited customization", "Basic design only"]}
        affiliateUrl={affiliates.durable.affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates.durable.commission}
        ctaText="Try Durable Free"
      />
      <Card
        title="10Web + WooCommerce"
        score="8.8"
        rating="Best for Online Ordering"
        pros={["Full e-commerce for delivery", "WordPress restaurant plugins", "Reservation systems available", "Scalable for multi-location"]}
        cons={["Requires WordPress knowledge", "Longer setup time", "Need WooCommerce extensions"]}
        affiliateUrl={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
        ctaText="Try 10Web Free"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">What Restaurants Need</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Essential Features</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>- Mobile-friendly menu display</li>
            <li>- High-quality food photos</li>
            <li>- Location/map integration</li>
            <li>- Click-to-call for reservations</li>
            <li>- Hours of operation prominent</li>
            <li>- Fast loading (mobile users)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Nice-to-Have Features</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>- Online ordering/delivery</li>
            <li>- Table reservations system</li>
            <li>- Gift card sales</li>
            <li>- Event/catering booking</li>
            <li>- Customer reviews display</li>
            <li>- Social media integration</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Durable AI for Restaurants</h2>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Why It Works for Restaurants</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Durable is AI generates restaurant-specific content: menu sections, cuisine descriptions, location info, ambiance descriptions. All from a single prompt.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          I tested with "Italian restaurant in downtown Portland" and got:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>Full homepage with hero image</li>
          <li>Menu section with Italian dishes</li>
          <li>About page with story</li>
          <li>Contact page with map placeholder</li>
          <li>Reservations CTA (links to external)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          All in under 30 seconds. Impressive for speed, less so for customization.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What is Missing</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          No built-in online ordering. You would need to integrate:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>UberEats/DoorDash buttons</li>
          <li>Toast POS integration</li>
          <li>External reservation system (OpenTable)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Best For</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Small restaurants, food trucks, cafes that need a web presence fast but use third-party services for ordering/reservations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">10Web + WooCommerce for Restaurants</h2>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Why It Works for Restaurants</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Full WordPress ecosystem means restaurant-specific plugins:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>WooCommerce for online ordering</li>
          <li>RestaurantPress for menu management</li>
          <li>Five Star Restaurant Reviews</li>
          <li>WpReservations for table booking</li>
          <li>Food menu plugins galore</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Build exactly what you need. WordPress restaurant themes are mature and feature-rich.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">The Trade-off</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Setup time. Durable: 30 seconds. 10Web restaurant site: 4-8 hours minimum.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          But you get full control, online ordering, reservations, scalability. Worth it for serious restaurants.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Best For</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Established restaurants, multi-location chains, venues wanting full control over ordering and reservations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-lg">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Other Options</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer (7.5/10)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Great design, but manual work. No restaurant-specific features. Use if you want a beautiful custom site and do not mind building menus manually.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Squarespace (8.5/10)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Excellent restaurant templates. Built-in menus. No AI but covers restaurant needs well. Higher price point.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Wix Restaurants (8.0/10)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Dedicated restaurant features including online ordering. No AI features. Solid choice if you do not need speed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Essential Restaurant Website Features</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. Mobile-First Menu</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">70% of customers check menus on phones. PDF menus are dead. Use HTML menus that are readable, zoomable, and fast-loading.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. High-Quality Food Photos</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">People eat with their eyes. Invest in professional food photography. Display prominently above the fold on mobile.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. Click-to-Call Reservations</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Mobile users should tap once to call. No copying phone numbers. Big, tappable phone button in header.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Location & Hours Prominent</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Address, hours, map should be visible without scrolling. Customers check these first.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">5. Fast Loading (Under 3 Seconds)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Hungry customers are impatient. Optimize images, use caching, test on 4G. Slow sites lose customers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Final Recommendation</h2>

      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Start with Durable AI</strong> if you need a restaurant site today. Free to try, builds in seconds, covers essentials.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Choose 10Web + WooCommerce</strong> if online ordering matters. More work, but you get full e-commerce for delivery/takeout.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Either way, prioritize: mobile menu, food photos, click-to-call, location/hours visible above fold. Everything else is secondary.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8">Both have free trials. Test with your menu and location.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <AffiliateCTA
            href={affiliates.durable.affiliateUrl}
            commission={affiliates.durable.commission}
            label="Try Durable for Restaurants"
            className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg"
          />
          <AffiliateCTA
            href={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
            commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
            label="Try 10Web for Restaurants"
            className="bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg"
