          <p class="text-gray-700">Most restaurants use OpenTable, Resy, or similar. Add "Book a Table" button linking to your system. Durable and 10Web both support this.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How do I handle menu updates?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Durable: Edit content in their editor. 10Web: WordPress makes it easy, or use restaurant menu plugins. Both support frequent updates.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Should I include prices on my website menu?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Generally yes. Customers expect transparency. Update regularly. For high-end restaurants, omit prices if that fits your branding.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What about delivery integration?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Unless you build with 10Web/WooCommerce, you will use third-party (UberEats, DoorDash). Add "Order Online" buttons linking to your platform.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-lg">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">You May Also Like</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
